commit.message: fixed some issues with crashing after importing photo
Included box in toString() for both Line.java and Region.java; changed BoundingBox.java's toString to have a lowercase b (similar to how it is formatted in the .json file)

Many Features Implemented in OCRClient.java, Region.java, Line.java, and Word.java

OCRClient.java
- (at least for example1-out.json), all important groups in a passed-in .json file
  is stored successfully
- It also prints all the contents

Region.java, Line.java, Word.java
- For Region.java and Line.java, included BoundingBox parameter in constructor
- Overridden toString() to cleanly organize all of the data
Client is now able to parse through and read all of the text items in a .json file created by Azure OCR; also included an example .json file to test it with
Wrote up a simple text file explaining Azure OCR in relation with the org.json.simple library
